               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-869" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-869" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-869" type="surname" value="THORNTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-869" type="given" value="HEKEY AUSTRALIA"></interp>HEKEY AUSTRALIA THORNTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Camberwell. In the beginning of April I left my coat in a cupboard at Mr. Searle's—I lost it—this is it (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. MELLER</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had you the key of the cupboard? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I used to leave it with Mr. Searle, and charged him with, the loss—another gentleman kept his coat in the same locker—there was only one key—I think he had it, as Mr. Searle had not—the constable gave me the coat—I know it by its appearance, and by one button having been torn, which I had sewn up—I found the cupboard doors open—the prisoner used to get the boats ready for us.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-870" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-870" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-870" type="surname" value="WINSTONE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-870" type="given" value="EDWARD FREDERICK"></interp>EDWARD FREDERICK WINSTONE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am clerk to George Searle and another, boat-builders. The prisoner was in their service, and had opportunities of going to this room—we missed this coat, and others.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How many other persons has Mr. Searle employed there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Only the prisoner and another in that yard—the prisoner has been there five or six years, I believe; but he has been dishonest once before—I have had no quarrel with him—I have not seen him wear this coat—it is a superior one.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-871" type="witnessName">
